<br>
I had never any real inclination to start another class.<br>
<br>
I am a 53 druid.  Healing druid.<br>
<br>
But, I started a baby DE Wizard.<br>
<br>
I know, I know, I should have started a Cleric, Warrior, or Enchanter.<br>
<br>
But I do not want to play any of those classes.<br>
<br>
I don't like pets, to much trouble.<br>
<br>
I love the ability to port.<br>
<br>
I love to nuke, and know when and when not to already(from a druid's pov that is).<br>
<br>
But....<br>
<br>
But....<br>
<br>
Reading this board, you seem to have the same problems that druids have.  But I have never seen a 50+ Wizard get tossed out of a group.<br>
<br>
And man, are Wizards fragile in the beginning or what?<br>
<br>
Well, I am going back to killing Skellies in Nek right now(which is one bad noob zone, btw).<br>
<br>
