Playing a Wizard is a tough challenge, but I truely love what I do.<br>
<br>
I never have to go into a group asking what my role is.  I don't have to watch my group members health bar every last second (Yes, you do need to watch them), I sit back, wait until I'm needed, and unleash hell.<br>
<br>
<br>
BOOM!  That's all I do.  I make a large dent in what's left of a mobs HP.  It's done quickly and effectively.<br>
<br>
I don't have indoor restrictions (I had my group ooohing and ahhing when I whipped out a rain spell indoors the other day), so I am just at home (from a class perspective) in a dungeon or in the Karanas.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
